resource.chars: On the Ieland of Great Britaire
Hail Queen of Isles w omely Plenty Crownt
For Ast for arms for daunttess sons renound
The boistons Ocean which around shee roars,
Pofts all the Wealth of India to thy shores;
With Commerce tilld thy fofty cities shine
And fall the products of the Globe are thene.
Whe would trust to such weak eye
On he goes post wondrour wise
Drainy are the Interludes which Janey makes:
When Monarch Reason sleeps, this minie waker,
Compounds a medly of disjointed Things,
O Court of Cobleds or a Mob of Kings
A Temper vord of heat or passion;
Not over Lond, yet ever kind:
A lively Cit a Judyment lear;
It breart with tendiest Passions warm,
Bee there the Belasy in the wite
with whom I spend my term of Life.
